Parliament, Wednesday, 13 May 2020 – The Portfolio Committee on Small Business Development, together with the Select Committee on Trade and Industry, Economic Development, Small Business Development, Tourism and Employment and Labour will this afternoon be briefed by the Department of Small Business Development on its strategic plan for the Medium Term Strategic Framework for 2020-2025, as well as Annual Performance Plan for the 2020/21 financial year.
	
	Additionally, the Portfolio Committee on Communications will be briefed in the evening by the Department of Communications and Digital Technologies, together with the South African Broadcasting Corporation (SABC) on their annual performance plans for the 2020/21 financial year.
	
	Details of the meetings are as follows:
	Portfolio Committee on Small Business Development, and Select Committee on Trade and Industry, Economic Development, Small Business Development, Tourism and Employment and Labour
	Date:  Wednesday, 13 May 2020
	Time:  15:00-18:00
	
	Portfolio Committee on Communications
	Date:  Wednesday, 13 May 2020
	Time:  18:00-21:00
	
	
	Members of the media who would like to be part of the meetings to observe may forward their contact details to Mr Mlindi Mpindi on 081 716 7329 for inclusion in the Parliament Communications Service WhatsApp group, where login details will be shared.
	
	Members of the public may get involved and follow committee sittings live on Parliament TV (DStv Channel 408), via live stream on Parliament YouTube channel and Twitter page on the links below. You may subscribe to the Parliament YouTube channel to receive instant notification of live feeds.
	
	Twitter: https://twitter.com/ParliamentofRSA
	Facebook: https://facebook.com/ParliamentofRSA
